reviews.text:
Service was 5/5 - waiter was very nice but never brought our condiments after 4 requests  -  but in this case kindness wins out.

Food was mediocre at best - more like cafeteria food - was underwhelming.

Atmosphere was neat and for this and service I‚Äôll probably try again -

Holy moly! Fantastic food. Got the armadillo eggs, the local sausage, and the brisket tacos. Outta this world. The sound system was excellent. Every syllable heard of the ultimate singer, Sam Riggs. Morgan and Courtney never let the cold drinks go empty, even when we had to move seats 3 times (owner had reserved seats for friends and our table was chosen after we were seatedü§™) The table next to us were a hand full (also friends of the owner who kept bumping us, moved their chairs closer to ours, blocked our view -we moved out from our table-  blocked us in, touched my hubs knee, and not once did they say "excuse me" or "so sorry") (they also stood in front of me periodically and just talked it up, not even listening to Sam Riggs -we drove 2.5 hours, and it was my birthday gift to go see Sam Riggs.) , but Courtney handled them with kid gloves. Met some locals who go three times a week for tacos, pizza, and their Friday night date. So cool!

The service was great and friendly. Our waiter took care of us the whole night and was quick. The food was okay, nothing over the top or special. The drinks were cold and tasted good. The live music was great.

Cool hang out place with a stage for live music
The front features an open, yet covered, deck with multiple types of seating for hanging out.

Entering the front door presents an open room with banquets, tables, high tops, and bar top seating for their full liquor, beer, and wine offerings. Plenty of options to choose from. They even have a nice stage to the left which hosts a variety of live artists rotated and advertised on their website. As far as the experience, this is so quite obviously a local favorite and for good reasons. If you don‚Äôt venture past this first room ,you will miss the amazing surprises offered beyond‚Ä¶

In a room behind the stage is a very large banquet/multi-use room (and apparently the kitchen is actually beyond that. This has the potential for various gatherings and can provide some privacy.

Now, proceeding to the rear of the main dining is an annex with secondary bar(s), pool tables, and seating. It doesn‚Äôt stop there, as you can then venture into a warehouse-style room with 0-10 organized and measured corn hole set ups. I have heard that this is a favorite place for company outings, fun tournaments, and quite obviously some league play. I have personally never seen so many people show up with their own carry or roll-on bags with personal equipment. I don‚Äôt think I will be playing anyone for $ around here!

We began with fried mushrooms and they were fresh and piping hot. So fresh and hot, there was a mandatory ‚Äòcooling off‚Äô period we needed to observe! Nice problem to have. We thoroughly enjoyed these little flavor explosions.

We then ordered the Jack Burger and the Spur Burger. One with fries and one with rings. Both came in a basket with a cool take on the paper liners, which are printed like newspaper pages with articles on cooking recipes, fishing techniques, etc. Super fun.

The Spur Burger had a good take on the combination of heat with jalape√±os and sweet with bacon, grilled onions, mushrooms and Swiss. My only hesitation here is their choice of meat, which seemed a little grey (weren‚Äôt asked about cook temp preference) and was was a little off the mark for both of us. Pics show that quite well.

Onion rings are a little too thick for my taste and the breading was way too thick (heavy) and mealy. Fries were just fine.

This wasn‚Äôt an occasion for us to sample the bar and such local specials, but I am quite sure this is a big draw of the popularity they enjoy. I will have to try that part another time. This is worth additional visits to participate in all the activities I mentioned that I saw but didn‚Äôt have time to join.

It is obviously public knowledge that this is an extremely dog friendly destination, and we witnessed multiple guests with their furry friends.

Everyone is greeted joyfully when they walk through the door and the entire staff we encountered were super polite, friendly, and attentive. High marks for our server, Cayla!

I came here to support Big Joe Walker's acoustic show. Walking in as the only POC, of course, there are looks & stares... some friendly... others not so much. As long as respect is reciprocated, I'm good.

Approaching what I assume to be the to-go counter, one of the male servers waived at me, welcoming me in. I really hate that I didn't catch his name, but he gave me phenomenal customer service the entire night!! Like... I never had to flag him down for anything. Even the food runners were very pleasant!!!

I ordered the chips & queso and had them add fresh pico & jalape√±os to give it that "rotel vibe." Otherwise, it would've just been chips & cheese. If there is a next time, I'll ask them to add ground beef if they have it.
‚≠êÔ∏è 4 out of 5

For my entree, I ordered the all-you-can-eat catfish and was pleasantly surprised!!!! Although a tad bit salty, it was well seasoned and fried to perfection with a cornmeal batter!!!!! Didn't care too much for the onion rings, but the hush puppies were more like hot water cornbread, and I enjoyed them!!
‚≠êÔ∏è 4.5 out of 5

For my drink, I had an Arnold Palmer with sweet tea and it was really good!
‚≠êÔ∏è 5 out of 5

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Krause
detailedReviews.text: Arrived here early Saturday evening. This being my first time here, I was a little disoriented where the entry door was.  FYI, they have a few parking spaces directly in front of the entry way stairs (guaranteed to be occupied), which made it difficult to see an access point when first rolling up.  We were formally welcomed at the door and told it was open seating and to sit wherever we liked.  It still being early, there were only about 50 people in the entire building, including staff.  We chose to sit at the bar, and we were immediately welcomed in & assisted with our drink orders. Drinks promptly served within the first 5 minutes of sitting down. The bar is NOT understaffed, they had at minimum 3 people taking orders and pouring drinks at any given moment..  The atmosphere at the Bar was pleasant with large TVs overhead and visible from multiple angles.  The bartenders and servers were all very polite, and quick to ask if we needed food menus.  We were given menus, and although the menu is not vast, is original and filled with various dishes that are not common everywhere (ie burger, fries etc. even though they do have their own spin on those as well).  Started with some ‚ÄúFrickles‚Äù (Fried Pickles) and were just that, battered and fried pickles, nothing crazy, not super salty, or BAMMED* with a crazy seasoning, very simple almost bland, with a small dip container of ranch dressing.  For an entree, I elected for the Cajun Pasta, which is absolutely AMAZING!!  The plate comes with ample amount of penne pasta, smothered in their own Cajun sauce, complete with peppers, grilled chicken, various spices and a BOLD, but not overpowering kick.  It was perfect for me, some Cajun dishes I have had in the past elsewhere have been too spicy to enjoy, however this was not spicy beyond the normal pallet.  The dish was complimented well with two pieces of soft buttery garlic bread, with just the right amount toasting around the edges.  Ended up having to get a to-go box to pack out the remaining pasta and sauce,  the dish is Very filling, My compliments to the kitchenüôèüèª.  The night ended well with no issues or drama, as my friend and I enjoyed a few more drinks, the staff ensured we had everything we needed and were enjoying our meal and drinks.  The check came due and surprisingly with an appetizer, 2 entrees and 5 adult beverages the bill was only slightly over $70.  By the time we were ready to leave, the place was alive with patrons. Every table was filled and the moment we got up from our spot at the Bar to leave, there was a couple that was laying in wait to immediately pounce at the bar location for fast drinks and immediate service. On our way out the door, it was clear that this place gets hopping as the sun goes down, the live band was preparing for their gig. Sadly we did not stick around for the live music, but we will be coming back in the near future.  Thanks for a Pleasant Evening Mule Barn!

Please do not bring your dog inside the establishment. I inquired about bringing my dog to the patio and was informed that it was permissible. However, the owner's dog then attacked my well-trained Doberman Pinscher.

This incident occurred on March 1, 2025, at 4:36 PM. We both remained calm and moved to the patio, where we had dinner at table #57. The owner displayed a lack of class and did not offer any apology. This lack of accountability reflects poorly on him as a business owner.

Your server apologized and mentioned that this incident had never happened before. While the hamburger was decent, the overall experience felt more like a bar with food rather than a pleasant dining environment.

To address your comment: You can't claim you don‚Äôt recall; you called out to your black lab to stop, and it followed us to the front door.

I'm not a level 7 reviewer who makes negative reviews lightly, but as a business owner and a native Texan, I understand how challenging it can be to run a business.
